      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): propagate llm.allowModelOverride to plugin subagent override policies (fixes #94289)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: LCM compaction fails with \"model override denied\" even though `plugins.entries.lossless-claw.llm.allowModelOverride` is `true`. The flag only takes effect after a config hot-reload (e.g. `doctor --fix`), not at normal gateway startup.\n- **Root Cause**: `setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies()` in `server-plugins.ts` only reads `entry.subagent.allowModelOverride` and `entry.subagent.allowedModels`, but the Lossless LCM compaction uses `entry.llm.allowModelOverride` and `entry.llm.allowedModels` (for `api.runtime.llm.complete`). The `llm` fields were never propagated into the override policy.\n- **Fix**: Extend the policy construction to also read `entry.llm.allowModelOverride`, `entry.llm.hasAllowedModelsConfig`, and `entry.llm.allowedModels` alongside the existing `entry.subagent` fields.\n- **What changed**:\n  - `src/gateway/server-plugins.ts` — merge `entry.llm` override fields into the plugin subagent override policy\n- **What did NOT change (scope boundary)**:\n  - `entry.subagent` fields — still read as before\n  - Policy authorization logic (`authorizeFallbackModelOverride`) — unchanged\n  - Config normalization (`config-normalization-shared.ts`) — already correctly normalizes both `subagent` and `llm`\n  - Hot-reload path — already worked; now startup path matches\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe config schema defines two independent override sections per plugin entry (`types.plugins.ts`):\n- `subagent.allowModelOverride` / `subagent.allowedModels` — for subagent runs\n- `llm.allowModelOverride` / `llm.allowedModels` — for `api.runtime.llm.complete` (used by LCM compaction)\n\nBoth are correctly normalized in `config-normalization-shared.ts`. However, `setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies()` only read from `entry.subagent`, leaving `entry.llm` fields ignored. LCM compaction checks the policy via `authorizeFallbackModelOverride()`, which only saw the `subagent`-based policy — hence \"model override denied\" for `llm`-configured plugins.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed (#94289)**: LCM compaction permanently blocked at startup because `llm.allowModelOverride` was not propagated to the plugin subagent override policy; fix now reads both `subagent` and `llm` override fields.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux, Node 22 — Vitest against `src/gateway/server-plugins.test.ts`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-plugins.test.ts`\n\n**Evidence before fix**:\n```text\nGateway startup:\n  setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies reads only entry.subagent\n  → llm.allowModelOverride = true is ignored\n  → policy has allowModelOverride: false\n  → LCM compaction: \"model override denied\"\n  \nAfter doctor --fix (hot-reload):\n  setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies re-runs with merged activation config\n  → config hot-reload path works (but is incidental)\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-plugins.test.ts\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  98 passed (98)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: `setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies()` now reads both `entry.subagent` and `entry.llm` override fields. A plugin configured with `llm.allowModelOverride: true` will have its override policy correctly set at startup, matching the behavior after hot-reload.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live end-to-end LCM compaction with a real Lossless plugin and Google provider; hot-reload path regression (already worked, tests confirm unchanged).\n\n**Repro confirmation**: Before the patch, `entry.llm.allowModelOverride` was silently ignored in the policy. After the patch, the policy merges both `subagent` and `llm` configs.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- Target test file: `src/gateway/server-plugins.test.ts`\n- Run: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-plugins.test.ts`\n- 98 existing tests pass with no changes\n\n## Review Findings Addressed\n\nNone yet — initial PR submission.\n\n## Merge Risk\n\n- **Risk**: Low — extends existing policy reading to include `llm` fields alongside `subagent` fields\n- **Affected code path**: Only `setPluginSubagentOverridePolicies()` which builds the override policy at startup/hot-reload\n- **Test coverage**: 98 existing gateway plugin tests pass\n- **Rollback**: Trivial — revert the 3 changed lines\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94289-llm-allowModelOverride",
